  schema:name "Baseball Cap as Crown and Code" ;
  schema:description "Look at someone's hat and you'll know a little bit about them. Not everything—but something. A place. A team. A vibe. A memory. A moment. The baseball cap doesn't cover identity. It broadcasts it. And that's been its secret power from the start." ;
